                        <locus target="#95v" facs="065">95v</locus><hi rend="margin">Mälʿa</hi>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#iv(erso) #iir(ecto) #iiv(erso) #iiir(ecto)" facs="002 003">Fols. iv(erso), iir(ecto), iiv(erso), iiir(ecto)</locus>
                    Prayer from Passion Week for the foot washing ceremony on Thursday, in a different hand
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    <locus target="#iiir(ecto)" facs="003">Fol. iiir(ecto)</locus>
                    Excerpt from <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5678CommemorationRoch">Commemorative note and hymn for St Roch
                                                  (Roqo)</title> for Miyazya 23 on Saint Roqo (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ሮቆ፡</foreign>), in a different hand
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    <locus target="#98v #99r #99v #100r #100v #101r #101v #102r #102v #103r #103v" facs="103 104 105 106 107">Fols. 98v, 99r, 99v, 100r, 100v, 101r, 101v, 102r, 102v, 103r, 103v</locus>
                    <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2260salota">Ṣalota kidān</title>. The text was printed in Ethiopia as <foreign xml:lang="gez">መጽሓፈ፡ ጸሎተ፡ ኪዳን። ሊጦን፡ ዘነግህ፡ መስተብቍዕ፡ ወዘይነግስ፡</foreign> (maṣḥāfa ṣalota kidān. liṭon za-nagh, mastabqwǝʿ, wazayǝnaggǝs). The beginning is dislocated and starts on <locus target="#102r" facs="106">102r</locus>. Written in a different hand
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                    Red paper strip with number 41 inside
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#96r" facs="100">Fol. 96r</locus>
                    the name of the owner and the scribe have been erased
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#25" facs="029">Fol. 25</locus>red string stitched into corner as navigation system
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <desc>
                    Numbered quires: quires 2–8 and 10–11 (the first folio of quire 9 has been painted over)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#2r #14r #21r #22r #34r" facs="006 018 025 026 038">folss. 2r, 14r, 21r, 22r, 34r, </locus>, etc.);
                      erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#64r" facs="068">64r, </locus>);
                      text has been removed (<locus target="#50v" facs="055">50v</locus>).
                    </desc>
                    </item>
